  "text": "An attractive candidate to prevent and treat retinal degeneration is the protein rod-derived cone viability factor (RdCVF), specifically expressed and secreted by photoreceptors [CITATION_1] . RdCVF is a product of the nucleoredoxin-like 1 (NXNL1) gene homologous to the family of thioredoxins known to possess strong antioxidative properties. This trophic factor has directly induced cone survival in animal models of recessive and dominant RP, and studies have documented functional rescue independent of the ",
